</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDED9750D4AFF8FFF4210E323DFCBE9" blockId="11.[151,1437,1048,2038]" box="[151,1436,1224,1246]" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">
<keyLead id="30907A400D4AFF8FFF4210E323DFCBE9" box="[151,1436,1224,1246]" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">- Aedeagus, in lateral view, curved on its base by almost 180º................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="3095C1D00D4AFF8FFF4210CC23DFCAB9" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">
<paragraph id="8BDED9750D4AFF8FFF4210CC23DFCA01" blockId="11.[151,1437,1048,2038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">
<keyLead id="30907A400D4AFF8FFF4210CC23DFCA01" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">
3(2). Subgenital plate distinctly narrowed only on apical third (
<figureCitation id="135AC5F00D4AFF8FFCC810CF251ACBC8" box="[797,857,1253,1276]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1820,1844]" captionTargetBox="[160,1430,637,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-87@2.[151,1436,630,1794]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Balacha ancora sp. nov., male. (1) Head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view. (2–6) Terminalia: (2) pygofer, lateral view (most macrosetae are missing but their insertion points were illustrated); (3) style, connective, and subgenital plate, ventral view (only the insertion points of plate macrosetae were illustrated); (4) style and connective, dorsal view; (5) paraphyses, dorsal view; (6) aedeagus and anal tube, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4425446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4425446/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
