<keyLead id="30907A400D4AFF8FFF42136423DFC8A9" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">
- Male pygofer with macrosetae distributed uniformly throughout disc; subgenital plate with long macrosetae (longer than half of basal width of plate); female sternite VII with slight median broad concavity on posterior margin; male length varying between 6.0 and 
<quantity id="4C9974900D4AFF8FFEFA13A2273BC8AA" box="[303,376,1928,1950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="11" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="7.6">7.6 mm</quantity>
and female between 7.1 and 
<quantity id="4C9974900D4AFF8FFD4513A2249AC8AA" box="[656,729,1928,1950]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" pageId="11" pageNumber="553" unit="mm" value="8.5">8.5 mm</quantity>
......................... 
