<keyLead id="30907A400D4AFF88FF4213CB23DFCFD3" lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="554" pageId="11" pageNumber="553">- Paraphyses bifurcated, but arms are not directed laterally in a 90º angle with stem; aedeagus with rows of dorsal small den- tiform processes; female pygofer, in lateral view, shorter than sternite VII; female sternite VII with median longitudinal fold originating from anterior margin; female sternite VIII sclerotized as a single plate; bases of first valvulae with anterior concavity in ventral view..................................................................................... 8</keyLead>
